0.4.0 (April 14th, 2026)

- Add: visibility-based data access segmentation (`public` / `private`) with FDA visibility validation, including CDA `doQuery` compatibility path handling (#21)
- Add: response format selection in query and doQuery using outputType, with csv and xls support (#20)
- Add: observability in health endpoint and Prometheus/OpenMetrics metrics endpoint `GET /metrics` (#90)
- Add: postgres db connection pool and env vars (`FDA_PG_POOL_MAX`, `FDA_PG_POOL_IDLE_TIMEOUT_MS`, `FDA_PG_POOL_CONN_TIMEOUT_MS`, `FDA_PG_POOL_DB_IDLE_TIMEOUT_MS`) (#28)
- Add: DuckDb now installs extension httpfs in a custom path defined by the new envVar FDA_OBJSTG_EXTENSIONS_DIR (#141)
- Fix: value of default params are checked when creating DA (#107)
- Fix: query operation is now REST-like using `GET /{visibility}/fdas/{fdaId}/das/{daId}/data` instead of `/query` (#62)
- Fix: object storage bucket name is now derived from `Fiware-Service` by replacing `_` with `-` (hard change); potential bucket-name collisions are an accepted restriction (#140)
- Fix: `fresh=true` queries now serialize dates as ISO 8601 strings and integers as numbers consistently with the cached Parquet path, across JSON, NDJSON and CSV outputs (#137)
- Fix: format negotiation done using the `Accept` HTTP standard mechanism (outputType is no longer supported, except in the Pentaho legacy operation) (#137)
- Fix: FDA now includes `servicePath` in Mongo unique index (`service + servicePath + fdaId`) and operational storage layout is now scoped as `/service/servicePath/fdaId/` (#132)
- Fix: forbids the usage of `/` as servicePath
- Fix: sanitize FDA retrieval payloads to avoid redundant/internal fields (#129)
  - `GET /{visibility}/fdas` returns `id` and omits `_id`, `fdaId`, `service`, `visibility`, `servicePath`
  - `GET /{visibility}/fdas/{fdaId}` omits those fields as they are already in request scope
- Remove: refreshPolicy type cron removed in favor of using only refreshPolicy type interval (#143)

0.3.0 (March 24th, 2026)

- Add: partitioned files, sliding window updates and scheduled deletes (#105)
- Add: fresh query mode (`GET /query?fresh=true`) with PostgreSQL execution and new runtime flag `FDA_ROLE_SYNCQUERIES` (#66)
- Add: fresh query concurrency guard via `FDA_MAX_CONCURRENT_FRESH_QUERIES` and `429 TooManyFreshQueries` (#66)
- Add: DA validation with FDA snapshot and query gating until first fetch completes (#97)
- Fix: move mongo data base name into mongo uri (#115)

0.2.0 (March 4th, 2026)

- Add: async background processing with Agenda and role-based runtime separation (FDA_ROLE_APISERVER / FDA_ROLE_FETCHER) (#63)
- Add: params array to DA creation (#60)
- Add: Pentaho CDA compatibility layer via POST /plugin/cda/api/doQuery with parameter adaptation and CDA response format support (#102)
- Add: validation fields in POST and PUT requests (ensure required, and only required, fields are present) (#97)
- Add: check for existing DA before creation in POST /das to prevent duplicates (#97)
- Add: use of header Fiware-servicePath for future access control (#61)
- Add: status, progress and lastFetch fields in FDAs to support async create/regenerate operations with progress tracking (#34)
- Add: NDJSON support for /query endpoint with streaming capability (#53)
- Add: health endpoint with e2e test coverage (#79)
- Add: logger component for initial, debug, info, warning and error level logs (adding new env vars `FDA_LOG_*`) (#14)
- Add: e2e testing based on testcointainers and supertest (partially #14)
- Fix: remove DA queries memory cache (#103)
- Fix: make description field optional in DA creation to match API specification (#97)
- Fix: use db connection pool for object storage and env var FDA_OBJSTG_MAX_POOL_SIZE
- Fix: make DA identifier immutable (cannot be updated via PUT) (#88)
- Fix: avoid FROM in DA queries; read_parquet source is injected internally (#37)
- Fix: remove attributes path and database from post /fdas action and database (#59)
- Fix: validation schema in configuration env vars like port (#43)
- Fix: docker compose pgsql options and context (#76)
- Fix: add lint to test
- Fix: move runtime dependencies (ajv, dotenv, lodash, @aws-sdk/client-s3) from devDependencies to dependencies in package.json (#72)
- Fix: improved error responses with proper status code and message (#30)
- Update: upgrade lint version (#79)
- Update: @duckdb/node-api dependency version from ~1.4.1-r.1 to ~1.4.4-r.1

0.1.0 (January 23rd, 2026)

- Initial release
